text: Lae City Football Club is a Papua New Guinean professional soccer club based in Lae. It was founded in 2014 and plays in the Papua New Guinea National Soccer League (PNGNSL).https://www.rsssf.org/tablesp/pngfound.html Lae City is the most successful soccer club in Papua New Guinea, having won the PNGNSL nine times. It is one of only two clubs to have ever won the PNGNSL, the other being Hekari United who won the first eight PNGNSL titles before Lae City won their first title in 2015 and have won every season since. ==References== Category:2014 establishments in Oceania Category:Soccer clubs in Papua New Guinea
